## 7. Build the payload (logic)

- Let **`OFF`** = offset from **first byte of the password buffer** to **saved EIP** (found in ¬ß6).
- libc addresses: **`SYSTEM`**, **`EXIT`**, **`BINSH`** (32-bit little-endian `struct.pack('<I', addr)`).
- Second line bytes (conceptually):

```text
"admin" + [padding to OFF] + p32(SYSTEM) + p32(EXIT) + p32(BINSH) + "\n"
```

Adjust if you keep a newline earlier in the line; **re-measure** so the **overwrite** still lands on **EIP**.

**Environment / alignment:** i386, **NX** and **ASLR** on the VM change what is allowed (ret2libc vs ROP vs leak). Follow your ISO and your teacher‚Äôs constraints.

